🟡 2. Queue Basics (DSA + SYSTEM DESIGN)
🧠 What is Queue?
6

👉 Queue = FIFO (First In First Out)

🔹 Operations
Enqueue → add
Dequeue → remove
Peek → view front
💻 Java Example
Queue<Integer> queue = new LinkedList<>();

queue.add(10);   // enqueue
queue.add(20);

queue.poll();    // dequeue
queue.peek();    // front
🧠 Real-World Usage

👉 Queue is used in:

Kafka messaging
Order processing systems
Notification services

💡 Example:
User places order → goes to queue → processed later

